    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To compare primary wound closure using a limberg flap with secondary (p.s.) wound healing
      following excision of a pilonidal sinus.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients who gave their informed consent who had excision of pilonidal sinus were randomly
      assigned to group A (primary wound closure with a Limberg flap) or to group B (open wound and
      p.s.wound healing).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
